description:
24 pages, full color. This series was intended to be a four-issue mini-series but was canceled after two issues.

Solicit for issue three:

To tempt the Fates is one thing... to out-and-out steal from them is sheer lunacy! Yet Orion must pit his destiny against some of the fiercest and most dangerous forces Olympus has to offer. As he peels away another veil of the gods' deceit, Orion is forced to walk the precipice between myth and mystery only to find himself at the very mouth of Hades.

Solicit for issue four:

There's no place like Hell. Orion's quest finally leads him to the Stygian depths of Hades itself where the demons he faces are both real and within himself. Persephone, Hermes, and the sons of Ares reveal their many faces in this final showdown as hard choices and shocking surprises tip the balance in the war for Olympus. This issue is the exciting conclusion of this epic four-part series.
name: Orion the Hunter

Creator-Owned Heroes is a 40-page monthly comic from Image Comics started by Jimmy Palmiotti and Steve Niles in June 2012.

Through their Facebook page the creators even interact with the fans for feedback and post previews of upcoming stories.

description:
In 2012, the Mayan doomsday prophecy is coming to pass, and the end of the world makes for strange allies. Vampirella, Red Sonja, Kulan Gath, Dracula, Eva, Herbert West The Re-Animator, Alan Quatermain, Athena, Dorian Gray, Purgatory, Pantha and many more choose sides and clash in battles that will decide the fate of the Earth and all of mankind. Will the forces of good be able to stop the end of days? Or will an army of darkness rise? A seven-issue, SELF-CONTAINED event! That's right, fans, no spinoffs, no add-ons, just seven issues of all out, apocalyptic warfare! Be there for the first crossover spanning the Dynamite line...before it's too late! DYNAMITE'S MOST POWERFUL AND AMBITIOUS CROSS-OVER EVER!

description:
Super-powered teenager Peter Stanchek is on a dangerous path. Skipping across the country in a desperate attempt to stay one step ahead of the authorities, Peter quickly realizes that he's a psionically-charged 'Harbinger' with the potential to reshape the course of human history. But Peter's plight has not gone unnoticed. Respected philanthropist and fellow Harbinger, Toyo Harada is about to offer Peter the chance at the things for which the boy has always longed -- family, inner peace, self-control -- and induct him into a secret network of conspiracy and subversion known as the Harbinger Foundation. Now Peter begins his long road towards a destiny that will shake the very foundations of the Valiant Universe. His first lesson? All power comes with a price.

Continued in Harbinger: Omegas (2014) and, later on, Imperium (2015-current).

The series also featured the following one-shots and zero issues, respectively:

  • Harbinger #0 (see listing below)
  • Harbinger: Bleeding Monk #0 (2014)
